08/08/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Gani Malushi, the Kruja police department chief, died of gunshot wounds Thursday (7 August).
Malushi was critically wounded Wednesday when two individuals shot at his vehicle.
His driver, widely believed to be the target of the assassination, was killed.
The perpetrators have not been identified or taken into custody.
Meanwhile, Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi and Democratic Party of Kosovo head Hashim Thaqi met with former Albanian Foreign Minister Ilir Meta in Saranda.
The two sides concluded that security in the region needs to be improved.
(ATA, Albanian Daily News, BBC - 07/08/03)
